Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until lightly golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, divide potatoes between two sheets; roast on top and middle racks.)

While potatoes roast, finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Mince @Jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Quarter @Lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, jalapeño, juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: Not a fan of spicy food? Feel free to add as little or as much jalapeño as you like.

Form @Ground Beef{10%ounce} into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Meanwhile, halve @Potato Buns{2}; toast directly on oven rack until golden.

Meanwhile, place @Queso Blanco{3%ounce} in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}; cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until warmed through, ~{25-30%seconds}; stir.

> TIP: If necessary, microwave for 5-10 seconds more.

Fill buns with @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce} (use about half a bag per bun), patties, queso blanco, and half the pico de gallo.

Divide burgers and potatoes between plates. Top potatoes with remaining pico and @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.